lish: variant of   Williams  ."]},{"name":"Willimas","meanings":["Altered form of English   Williams  ."]},{"name":"William","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Middle English personal name <i>William</i>, <i>Willam</i>, <i>Willem</i>, an Old Picard and Norman French form of ancient Germanic <i>Willihelm</i>, composed of the elements <i>wil-</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm-</i> ‘helmet, protection’. This Norman personal name became widely used in England, Scotland and Wales after the Conquest, mainly no doubt in honor of the Conqueror himself. By the 13th century it had already become the most popular personal name in England. A Parisian form of the name <i>Guillaume</i> was also sometimes used (see   Gillam  ), which in medieval Wales was adopted as <i>Gwilym</i> (see   Gwilliam  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Guillaume  ."]},{"name":"Pulliam","meanings":["Welsh and English: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap William</i> ‘son of William’ (see   Williams  ). This surname is very rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Willaims","meanings":["Altered form of English   Williams  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Williams I was born about 1405, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom as the son of Isabella Drew. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"abt 1405–":"umbes 1405–Surnud","1405–Male":"1405–Surnud","1432–1493":"1432–1493","–Female":"Surnud","abt 1405":"umbes 1405","1432":"1432","1493":"1493","1405":"1405","Silford, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1405–":"noin 1405–Kuollut","1405–Male":"1405–Kuollut","1432–1493":"1432–1493","–Female":"Kuollut","abt 1405":"noin 1405","1432":"1432","1493":"1493","1405":"1405","Silford, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1405–":"environ 1405–Décédé","1405–Male":"1405–Décédé","1432–1493":"1432–1493","–Female":"D